<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <%- include('../partials/head'); %>
</head>

<body class="container">

    <header>
        <%- include('../partials/header'); %>
    </header>

    <main>
        <div class="jumbotron">
            <h1>About</h1>
            <p>This site is a simple example of templating using EJS and Express.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Extra content below the jumbotron, still styled consistently -->
        <section class="content">
            <h2>What is this project?</h2>
            <p>
                This project demonstrates how to build pages using reusable partial templates
                (head, header, footer) and render content dynamically with EJS.
            </p>

            <h2>Why use EJS?</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Reusable layout:</strong> header/footer are shared across pages.</li>
                <li><strong>Dynamic output:</strong> you can inject variables from Express.</li>
                <li><strong>Cleaner code:</strong> avoid copy/pasting the same HTML.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Quick facts</h2>
            <p>
                Page rendered at: <strong>
                    <%= new Date().toLocaleString() %>
                </strong>
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <%- include('../partials/footer'); %>
    </footer>

</body>

</html>
``